LONDON (AP) — England captain Owen Farrell was ruled out of the rugby test against Tonga on Saturday a day after testing positive for the coronavirus.England made the announcement just an over an hour before kickoff at a sold-out Twickenham.Farrell was replaced at flyhalf by George Furbank and the captaincy was passed to Courtney Lawes.British and Irish Lions flyhalf Marcus Smith remained in the reserves after an unspecified leg injury limited his training this week.Furbank was in the squad as a fullback who can cover flyhalf, and his three previous starts were at fullback, although he made a cameo appearance at flyhalf against Canada in July.He was replaced on the bench by Mark Atkinson.Farrell tested positive on Friday and was immediately isolated, a day after an unnamed member of Eddie Jones’ staff tested positive for COVID-19. Farrell and everyone in the camp underwent more tests on Friday.England has yet to say whether Farrell will be available for the rest of England’s autumn fixtures against Australia and South Africa.___More AP sports: https://apnews.com/hub/apf-sports and https://twitter.com/AP_Sports